articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 47 - The Birth of the Ultimate Flaming Dragon!
articles.description: The Mon Colle Knights are in the fight of their lives against the demonic magic of Reda, the Angel of Red Death.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 44 - The Wandering Tan-Tan Detector
articles.description: Some Kobold scientists retrieve Collection's abandoned Tan-Tan-Tanuki Detector and bring it to life.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 42 - Clash! Ichiroubei Versus Collection
articles.description: It's Ichiroubei versus Collection, one on one, as they search for a Mon Mon Item in a land of scorching heat.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 41 - Luke's Lovey-dovey Mission!
articles.description: While on a journey as part of their magical training, Luke tries to find an item that will give him the courage to tell Beginner how he feels about her.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 40 - Uneasiness of the Highest Order!
articles.description: Rokuna must continue the fight, even when it seems Mondo is gone for good.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 39 - The Great Battle Beyond the Wave!
articles.description: Tiamat sponsors a water-based monster battle, with a Mon Mon Item in the balance, but something lurks behind the scenes...

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 37 - We're Useful Valkyries!
articles.description: The Valkyrie Girl Recruits return and despite their clumsiness, the Knights try to help them become full-fledged members.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 7 - From Stylish to Orction?!
articles.description: After gaining major stress weight, Collection fits right in as the self-proclaimed king of the Orcs.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 36 - One Giant Baseball Player!?
articles.description: With a Mon Mon Item at stake, the Knights play baseball against Collection, who has a giant on his team.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 31 - Mermaid Princess of the Sea Castle!
articles.description: The Knights enjoy their time at the Pearl Mermaid Princess's castle until Collection causes a seaquake.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 27 - Right On With a Leprechaun!
articles.description: Count Collection and company finally get a cute mascot of their own, a Leprechaun who likes to blow up their ship.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 23 - The Coveted June Bride!
articles.description: The Knights get caught between a trio of miniature hapless Valkyrie recruits and a Weretiger who demands a bride.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 19 - My Little Brother, Kenta-kun!
articles.description: Mondo gets jealous when Rokuna "adopts" Kenta, a young centaur, as a little brother.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 14 - Does the King Like It Hot?
articles.description: Mondo and Rokuna encounter a talkative penguin at a hot spring, as you do, but party poopers Collection and company aren't far behind.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 10 - Oh, My Washed-up Friend!
articles.description: When Mondo and Collection are washed up on a desert island together, they become friends?!

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 9 - Even Jahnay Tries Hard!
articles.description: When the Knights are between a Roc and a hard place, only Jahnay can save the day.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 6 - Run, It's an Air Race!
articles.description: Mondo on a baby Pegasus vies against Collection riding a Hippogriff in a thrilling air race.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 5 - Blooming Love Senorita!
articles.description: The Knights come upon a land of feuding cactus people, with two young lovers caught in the middle.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 2 - Jahnay the Lovestar!
articles.description: Mondo and Rokuna help a girl search for a lost monster in water element territory.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 48 - Showdown! The Angel of Red Death's Trap
articles.description: Reda abducts Rokuna and takes her to the demonic domain.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 38 - The Wind and Rokuna's Fairy Tale
articles.description: Rokuna's dream comes true when she gets to meet fairies in Six Gates, but Collection spoils things by unleashing Bahamut, an ornery wind dragon.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 35 - The Mightiest Macho Man!
articles.description: Somehow Collection becomes a macho man and enters the Mightiest Man Contest, a free-for-all brawl.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 33 - Vampire of the Haunted House!
articles.description: Mondo and Rokuna are trapped inside a haunted house, hunted by the vampiric creature Collection has become.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 32 - Operation: Rose Room
articles.description: Collection and company secretly help the Mon Colle Knights find a Mon Mon Item so they can steal it from them.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 28 - Waveriding Summer at Paradise Beach
articles.description: Mondo enters the grueling Gillmen Triathlon.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 26 - Rainbow Emerging From a Break in the Darkness
articles.description: Sacher, the fallen angel, tries to prove that the Mon Colle Knights would betray their comrades.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 25 - Your Smile, Again and Again
articles.description: Collection uses the Mirror of Lies to change the forms of Ichiroubei and the Knights.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 24 - Is Food Cooked With Love a Little Extreme?!
articles.description: It's the Knights versus Count Collection and company again, but this time in a cooking battle!

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 22 - How About Some Terrible Luck, a Great Misfortune, or Unhappiness?
articles.description: Both the Knights and Collection are plagued by a malicious, ill luck-bringing Gremlin.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 18 - Punch-punch to a Knockout!
articles.description: Count Collection and company are kidnapped by Goblins and forced to become maids.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 15 - Roar at the Night Sky, Dragons!
articles.description: The Knights deal with a Frost Dragon causing unseasonable blizzards.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 8 - Beginner-chan Is an Evocater?!
articles.description: The Knights meet Beginner-chan, a girl who has the skill to summon monsters at will.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 46 - Explosive Heat! Fire Dragon
articles.description: Mondo and Rokuna want to make friends with Fire Dragon, but it only seems interested in burning them to a crisp.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 49 - The Gathering of the Six Mon Mon Items!
articles.description: Mondo and his allies journey to the Charon Zone to rescue Rokuna, but they fall one by one before the might of the Terror Dragon.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 50 - The Vanishing World of Six Gates
articles.description: The world of Six Gates is about to be wiped out as the Master of Time returns.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 43 - Cleaning Kikimora
articles.description: The Mon Colle Knights help the neat freak fairy, Kikimora, when Collection steals her magic broom.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 16 - Is There Something in the Arisona Desert?!
articles.description: The Mon Colle Knights finally find a Mon Mon Item, but its Earth Dragon owner doesn't want to give it up.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 13 - Gokumare's Big Adventure!
articles.description: Lonely 5th grade teacher Namiko Gokumare hitches a ride to Six Gates and even helps the Knights in an adventure.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 12 - Show Me Your Smile Once More!
articles.description: Much to Rokuna's fury, Mondo seems to fall for the Diva of the Garden, an elf princess who's bugged by a certain problem.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 45 - Gokumare's Ultra-Grand Adventure!
articles.description: Gokumare meets the man of her dreams in a "magical forest," but gets more than she bargains for.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 34 - The Huge Lovestar?!
articles.description: A giant, ravenous Jahnay goes on the rampage in a forest village.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 30 - Mon Colle Knights' Magic Training
articles.description: Collection tricks the lovelorn Luke into attacking Mondo.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 29 - Welcome to Six Gates Academy
articles.description: Mondo and Rokuna go to Six Gates Academy to learn how to be monster-summoning evocaters.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 21 - Sky City Showdown!
articles.description: It's a happy reunion with Pegasus on Cloud Island, interrupted by a powerful giant monster.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 20 - Black Wings Flutter in the Dark!
articles.description: Mondo is stalked by a demonic fallen angel.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 17 - Justice Prevails?! Mon Colle Knights
articles.description: It's the Knights versus Collection in an all-out monster battle over the second Mon Mon Item.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 11 - Dig It Up, Get Lost and Drop It!
articles.description: The Knights search for a Mon Mon Item in ancient ruins, only to find plenty of deathtraps and hole-digging Kobolds.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 4 - Mermaid Magic, Bippity-boppity-boo!
articles.description: To save the Mermen Tabernacle Choir, Rokuna has to possess a giant frog monster... but she hates frogs.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 3 - Clash of the Giants!
articles.description: A battle of the behemoths takes place in a forest, with the Mon Colle Knights and Count Collection controlling giant monsters.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 1 - Fly to the World of Six Gates!
articles.description: 5th graders Mondo Ohya and Rokuna Hiiragi, along with her genius scientist father, Ichiroubei, journey to Six Gates, a world full of monsters and powerful items.

articles.title: Mon Colle Knights - Episode 51 - That Brilliance Is a Diamond
articles.description: It's the final showdown between the Mon Colle Knights and the extra-dimensional Ouroboros.
